<h1>Calendar Help</h1>

<p>
    The calendar model helps you manage calendars and their associated events.
</p>

<h2>Permissions Required</h2>

<p>
    Each calendar had three permissions which determine who can change what in
    that particular calendar.
</p>

<dl>
    <dt>admin</dt>
    <dd>
        allows you to change the attributes of the <strong>calendar</strong>
        itself
    </dd>

    <dt>view</dt>
    <dd>
        allows you to see the list of <strong>events</strong> in the admin
        interface
    </dd>

    <dt>edit</dt>
    <dd>
        allows you to add/edit and delete <strong>events</strong> from this
        <strong>calendar</strong>
    </dd>
</dl>

<h2>Entities</h2>

<h3>Calendar</h3>

<p>
    A calendar has the following attributes:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>name</li>
    <li>title</li>
    <li>description</li>
</ul>

<h3>Event</h3>

<p>
    Each event is associated with a calendar.
</p>

<p>
    An event has the following attributes:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>name</li>
    <li>title</li>
    <li>intro</li>
    <li>description</li>
    <li>type</li>
    <li>startts</li>
    <li>endts</li>
    <li>allday</li>
    <li>location</li>
    <li>link</li>
</ul>

